{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-3765].
  {panel}

There is no limit set to adding columns, so you can keep adding ad infinitum. Once created, the deletion is so slow that the only way to undo the work is to delete the rapidview. See how fun the attached image is

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-3627].
  {panel}

Configure comment/description fields to use wiki markup renderer. Then add a paragraph with
{ noformat } tags around it. It will be displayed as a scrollable inline element.

Clicking on the scroll bar activates editing, which is not the desired behaviour

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-3611].
  {panel}

The chart itself is useful, but if you don't for the life of you know what the timeframe is youre looking at, the chart becomes useless. I suggest changing the default timescale to be longer (less tickmarks) to avoid the overlapping of dates.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-3573].
  {panel}

In combination with a keyboard modifier, provide the ability to transition an issue when statuses are on the same column on a board. Currently, users have to resort to the "." shortcut or the detail's view Workflow actions drop down. It would be nice to support the drag & drop UI paradigm for all available transitions.
